> my two cents days ... change your filter at every oil change.  it's only
> a $3 to $5 part.

yup, why put new oil thru a dirty filter,  if I could only change one
or the other I would seriously consider it the filter.

also why I use the best oil I can find.  Oil is cheap compared to a
new engine, and occasional service may be the most severe usage for
any piece of machinery.

